This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with improving the effectiveness of query analysis and retrieval of relevant products in commerce search. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning algorithms to learn from user behavior and structured data sources, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of structured data sources such as product catalogs also suggests that the paper could belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of its approach using a Mechanical Turk study, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
